comments.text:
I love watching comedies from 1999-2003 they all have this sort of crude 
style to them that was very new because they're just playing on (at the 
same time making fun) the old cliches in comedies from before.

I think its started with American Pie because Bring it On is just the PG 13 
version of it and Not Another Teen Movie was the edgy' version ﻿
comments.author: peeeons

comments.text:
+Shadohz75
For sure.  Objectively the 80s movies are better.  I think that the 
90s-2000s movies happened partly as a reaction against the painful 
earnestness of some of the 80s movies, which is why they are so easily 
parodied.  Also there was perhaps a cultural shift, whereby people didn't 
really feel the social issues covered by the 80s films needed to be trotted 
out again. 

Since I was in my teens-early 20s in the latter era, however, those movies 
win out on pure nostalgia, which is a hard thing to beat, and maybe because 
I was already such an introspective person that the gross-out comedies were 
like a relief.
comments.author: valinor100

comments.text:

Don't get me wrong. I loved the 90-2000 ish movies. The 80's movies just 
have something these movies lack... reliability AND heart.
